Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "keri" in different forms and positions with translations in English:

1. *Keri* je srećno skakala po travi. (The puppy happily jumped on the grass.)
2. Učiteljica je *keri* napisala peticu u dnevniku. (The teacher gave the student an A in the grade book.)
3. *Kerić* je krenuo u šetnju sa svojim vlasnikom. (The little dog went for a walk with its owner.)
4. Moja prijateljica je kupila *keru* u azilu. (My friend adopted a dog from the shelter.)
5. *Keru* je bilo hladno pa ju je vlasnik obukao u jaknu. (The dog was cold, so its owner dressed it in a jacket.)
6. Kada su otvorili vrata, *keri* je srećno skočio u zagrljaj svoje gazdarice. (When they opened the door, the dog happily jumped into its owner's arms.)
7. *Kerica* je zalajala na prolaznike ispred kuće. (The female dog barked at passersby in front of the house.)
8. Kad god dođem u goste, *kera* me dočeka na vratima. (Whenever I come over, the dog greets me at the door.)
9. *Keru* je potrebna redovna šetnja kako bi bio zdrav. (The dog needs regular walks to stay healthy.)
10. Moj deda ima mnogo priča o svom starom *keru*. (My grandpa has many stories about his old dog.)